  "text": "The electrophoretic mobilities of standard proteins of known molecular mass [aldolase (154 kDa), BSA (66 kDa), ovoalbumin (47 kDa) and cytochrome c (12 kDa)] were used to estimate the native molecular masses of plastidic algal sPPases on a series of non-denaturing (native) PAGE gels with different polyacrylamide percentages, as described by Hedrick and Smith [CITATION_1] .",
